framework.multi
Class MultiConstraint

java.lang.Object
  framework.Constraint
      framework.multi.MultiConstraint
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable
Direct Known Subclasses:
MultiBinaryConstraint
public abstract class MultiConstraint
extends Constraint

A MultiConstraint is a constraint among Variables that could be MultiVariables. Every MultiConstraint is "implemented" one or more lower-level constraints - see, e.g., the AllenIntervalConstraint.

Author:
Federico Pecora

propagateImmediately

public boolean propagateImmediately()
A MultiConstraint can be scheduled for propagation immediately (as soon as it is added) or later. This is used internally by the ConstraintSolver to delay propagation of a MultiConstraint in cases where the underlying constraints should be propagated first. By default, MultiConstraints are propagated immediately.

Returns:
true iff this constraint should be propagated as soon as possible.
